Hi Folks,
              I have just installed fedora core 5 and am unabIe to install your tool so far. I used ddccontrol successfully with fedora core 4 and same hardware; nVidia 6800 with Samsung SyncMaster 960bf but am having some difficulty with the config script completing successfully. 

checking pci/pci.h usability... no
checking pci/pci.h presence... no
checking for pci/pci.h... no
configure: error: PCI utils headers not found, please install pci-utils.
[root@...78... ddccontrol-0.4.1]#

I do have the latest pci-utils package but it is not being seen for some reason

[root@...78... ddccontrol-0.4.1]# rpm -q pciutils
pciutils-2.2.1-1.2
[root@...78... ddccontrol-0.4.1]#

I don't know how to establish the link to the pci-utils to allow the configure script to execute successfully. Any help would be great. Thank you  -Winn



